  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop the<strong> brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 600ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>asparagus</strong> into rounds until you reach the tips, keeping the tips whole</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262-new-step-copy-1617899671661-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262-new-step-copy-1617899671661-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262-new-step-copy-1617899671661-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262-new-step-copy-1617899671661-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262-new-step-copy-1617899671661-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>arborio rice</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add the <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 1/3 of the <strong>vegetable stock</strong> and stir continuously until the stock has been absorbed into the rice</p><p>Add the <strong>asparagus rounds</strong>, then continue to add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong>, a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>risotto</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, roll the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> wedges</p><p>Grate the<strong> Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262-new-step-2-copy-1617899680113-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262-new-step-2-copy-1617899680113-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262-new-step-2-copy-1617899680113-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262-new-step-2-copy-1617899680113-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262-new-step-2-copy-1617899680113-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>reserved asparagus tips</strong> to one side of a baking tray, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 5-6 min or until the<strong> </strong>asparagus tips are nearly cooked and tender</p><p>After 5-6 min add the <strong>flaked almonds</strong> to the other side of the tray and cook for a further 2-3 min or until golden and toasted</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1262.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, remove the<strong> risotto</strong> from the heat and stir in the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Add the juice of 2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4]</span> <strong>lemon wedges</strong></p><p>Season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the risotto is looking a little dry</p>",
